Given the following program, identify all loop structures. Please write the identified lines (just copy the first line of code from this loop, e.g., for (xxx) {, while (xxx) {.) into a list: [a list of identified lines]. If no loop is identified, just give an empty list [].. The program is typedef char a;
typedef int b;
typedef unsigned c;
a fn1(a p1, a p2) { return p1 * p2; }
struct g {
  signed h;
};
b i;
struct g j;
b *fn2(c p1, b *p2, a p3) {
  for (p3 = 6; p3 != -7; p3--)
    j.h ^= fn1(p3, i) && 1L;
  return p2;
}
int main() { return 0; }
.
